<br>
They have the right to tell their children they needn't say &quot;under God&quot; if they're so inclined.<br>
<br>
They don't have the right to tell other people they <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> cannot</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> say it, however; and further, I question whether they should really be telling their own children &quot;There is no God.&quot;  Why not let them choose for themselves?<br>
<br>
<br>
I hardly think that any presence of religious belief in US government history has been overly negative.  To clarify before someone even brings up bad examples, I mean true belief, not someone using belief as an excuse.<br>
<br>
In regards to the separation of church and state, I'll refer to the post of mine a couple up.  I will grant you that I don't personally know any of our founding fathers, seeing as how it would be impossible.  As to reading their works and whatnot...I have done some of that.  There's a few pieces in particular, named &quot;The Declaration of Independence&quot; and &quot;The Constitution of the United States&quot;, which seem rather indicative to me that they believed in a God of higher being than any of any mortal, and a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> God</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that created us with certain rights.<br>
<br>
Am I calling for religious wars? No, I firmly believe in tolerance for all religions; some of my best friends are Jewish, Muslims, Hindus, Buddhists, Atheists, and Agnostics.<br>
<br>
yet none of them have any issues with &quot;under God&quot;.  Why do others feel so threatened as to wish to strip away the rights of the majority to simply buffer their own already intact rights? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/ujohnfraz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>John Fraz</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_yingyang.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 231<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(10/1/02 2:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=286.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://lneilsmith.com/tools/littlelogo.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Child abuse?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> I question whether they should really be telling their own<br>
