 Note carefully that they don't say that &quot;They are endowed by their creator, the Lord God, Jehova of the old testament, the father of our saviour the Lord Jesus Christ, with certain rights&quot;<br>
 They couldn't have said that, because too many of the people they needed to sign off on the new nation and its government wouldn't have allowed it because it went against their beliefs.<br>
<br>
 Again, look through the books &amp; stacks of letters they wrote, to see how they really felt about these things.<br>
<br>
 The whole point is that observing any one particular religious belief's way of worshipping is directly against the spirit of the constitution.<br>
 To some people, the very word &quot;god&quot; has too many connotations of the Abrahamic religions, and that's too narrow to include in any government sponsored facet of public life.<br>
 Simple fact, and only too narrow adherence to that particular religion and wanting to see it proselytised around leads people to think otherwise.<br>
